# Openable File Paths In Chat

Whenever you share a file (especially `.md`) or a filesystem path with the user,
make it openable from this Cursor session.

## Required format (Cloud-safe)

1. Prefer an **inline backtick path** — Cursor treats these as openable file
   references. In multi-root / Cloud VM workspaces, use the **absolute** path.
2. For a specific region, use a **code citation block**
   (` ```startLine:endLine:filepath ` `) so the user can jump to those lines.
3. If you mention several files, give **each** its own backtick path (or
   citation).
4. You may also add a normal GitHub `https://github.com/.../blob/<branch>/...`
   URL when the file is already pushed and the user needs a browser tab — that
   is additive, not a substitute for the workspace path.

## Forbidden (causes web 404 on cursor.com/agents)

Do **not** wrap workspace paths in markdown links with a leading-slash href:

- Bad: `[SPEC.md](/agent/repos/PLX_MC/artifacts/.../SPEC.md)`
  → browser goes to `https://cursor.com/agent/repos/...` → 404
- Bad: `[SPEC.md](file:///agent/repos/...)` as the only reference

Leading-slash markdown targets are **site-relative web URLs** on the Cloud
Agent web UI, not workspace open actions.

## Examples

Good:

- Draft SPEC: `/agent/repos/PLX_MC/artifacts/platform/2026-07-24-ds-gov-cloud-enforcement/SPEC.md`
- Kickoff report: `/agent/repos/PLX_MC/artifacts/platform/2026-07-24-ds-gov-cloud-enforcement/REPORT.md`
- (written in chat as backtick-wrapped absolute paths)

Also good for a region — use a citation fence with `startLine:endLine:filepath`.

Bad:

- `[SPEC.md](/agent/repos/PLX_MC/artifacts/.../SPEC.md)` (web 404 on Cloud)
- “See the SPEC in the orchestrator folder” (no path)
